{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838219489,"sessionID":"ses_287cd5c44ffeJcbaguZzPMUBRv","part":{"id":"prt_d7832aedf001rVttWOS3XIHIsI","messageID":"msg_d7832a497001ZrYtfR9HXv4FcC","sessionID":"ses_287cd5c44ffeJcbaguZzPMUBRv","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_fe665aef887843ba979669ed","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore AR-014 Valkey store","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project to find all files related to AR-014 (Valkey storage implementation) in pkg/store. I need to understand:\n\n1. What files exist in pkg/store/ directory\n2. What Valkey-related code has been implemented\n3. Any TODO comments, stubs, or incomplete implementations\n4. Any related test files\n5. Any documentation or notes about what was planned vs what was done\n\nSearch thoroughly in:\n- pkg/store/ directory\n- Any docs/ or notes/ directories\n- Any backlog, TODO, or planning files\n- Git history if available (git log --oneline related to valkey/store)\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of what was completed and what appears to be deferred/incomplete.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_287cd42f4ffeVB604oYQGNV0L1 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the AR-014 Valkey storage implementation. Here is my complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## AR-014: Valkey Storage Implementation -- Comprehensive Analysis\n\n### 1. Files in `pkg/store/` Directory\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store.go` | 35 | `Store` interface definition, `ErrNotFound`, `Storage()` accessor |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | 253 | **Valkey implementation** (AR-014) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` | 634 | **Valkey unit tests** (AR-014) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go` | 274 | Redis implementation (AR-013, reference) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis_test.go` | 583 | Redis unit tests |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/singleton.go` | 39 | Provider selection (`STORE_TYPE` env var), `sync.Once` singleton |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/singleton_test.go` | 85 | Singleton + provider selection tests |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/codec.go` | 19 | JSON encode/decode helpers for `SandboxInfo` |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/codec_test.go` | 111 | Codec round-trip tests |\n\n### 2. Valkey-Related Code Implemented\n\nThe Valkey implementation (`store_valkey.go`) is **fully implemented** with all 10 `Store` interface methods:\n\n| Method | Status | Implementation Details |\n|--------|--------|----------------------|\n| `Ping()` | **Complete** | Uses `B().Ping().Build()` via `Do()`, validates `\"PONG\"` response |\n| `GetSandbox()` | **Complete** | `B().Get().Key(key)`, `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` normalized to `ErrNotFound` |\n| `StoreSandbox()` | **Complete** | `DoMulti`: SETNX + ZADD expiry + ZADD activity; validates nil/zero ExpiresAt |\n| `UpdateSandbox()` | **Complete** | `B().Set().Key().Value().Xx()`, checks response == `\"OK\"` |\n| `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` | **Complete** | `DoMulti`: DEL + ZREM expiry + ZREM activity |\n| `ListSandboxes()` | **Complete** | ZRANGE 0 -1 on expiry index, individual GET calls per session ID, skips orphan members |\n| `ListExpiredSandboxes()` | **Complete** | ZRANGEBYSCORE with `-inf` to `before.Unix()`, limit support, orphan tolerance |\n| `ListInactiveSandboxes()` | **Complete** | Same pattern on `session:last_activity` ZSET |\n| `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` | **Complete** | EXISTS check, zero-time fallback to `time.Now()`, ZADD |\n| `Close()` | **Complete** | `v.cli.Close()` |\n| `newValkeyStore()` | **Complete** | Constructor with env var validation (ADDR, PASSWORD, DISABLE_CACHE, FORCE_SINGLE) |\n\n**Singleton integration** (`singleton.go`): `STORE_TYPE=valkey` branch is fully wired (lines 28-33).\n\n**Dependency**: `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.0.73` is present in `go.mod` (line 13).\n\n### 3. TODO Comments, Stubs, or Incomplete Implementations\n\n**Zero TODO/FIXME/STUB/HACK/XXX comments found** anywhere in `pkg/store/`. The codebase is clean of inline markers for incomplete work.\n\nHowever, the **design document** (`changes/AR-014/design.md`) explicitly lists these as **known limitations / future changes** (Section 8):\n\n| Deferred Item | Priority | Description |\n|---------------|----------|-------------|\n| TTL on session keys | P1 | No automatic TTL on session JSON keys; relies on GC controller for cleanup |\n| Hash tag support for Valkey Cluster | P2 | Keys do not use hash tags (`session:{cluster}:{id}`) for cluster slot affinity |\n| Metrics | P2 | No store operation latency or error rate metrics |\n| Integration tests with testcontainers-valkey | P2 | Tests use miniredis (Redis-compatible); no live Valkey integration tests |\n| MGET optimization for batch loads | P3 | `ListSandboxes`/`List*` methods use individual GET calls instead of MGET |\n\n### 4. Test Files\n\n**Valkey-specific tests** (`store_valkey_test.go`) -- **33 test functions**, all comprehensive:\n\n| Category | Test Functions |\n|----------|---------------|\n| Constructor validation | `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingAddr`, `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingPassword`, `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordNotRequired`, `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordRequiredTrue` |\n| Ping | `TestValkeyStore_Ping` |\n| GetSandbox | `TestValkeyStore_GetSandbox_NotFound`, `TestValkeyStore_GetSandbox_Found` |\n| StoreSandbox | `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_NilInfo`, `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry`, `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Success`, `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_RoundTrip`, `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Duplicate` |\n| UpdateSandbox | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_NilInfo`, `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_KeyNotExists`, `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_Success` |\n| DeleteSandbox | `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID_NonExistent` |\n| ListSandboxes | `TestValkeyStore_ListSandboxes`, `TestValkeyStore_ListSandboxes_Empty`, `TestValkeyStore_ListSandboxes_OrphanZSETMember`, `TestValkeyStore_MultipleSandboxes` |\n| UpdateSessionLastActivity | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_EmptySessionID`, `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound`, `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_Success`, `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime` |\n| ListExpiredSandboxes | `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_LimitZero`, `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_LimitNegative`, `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes`, `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_Limit`, `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanMember` |\n| ListInactiveSandboxes | `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_LimitZero`, `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_LimitNegative`, `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes`, `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_OrphanMember` |\n| Utility | `TestValkeyStore_Close`, `TestValkeyStore_SessionKey`, `TestValkeyStore_ErrNotFound_Is`, `TestValkeyStore_InterfaceCompliance`, `TestValkeyStore_StructFields` |\n| Score calculation | `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_ScoreCalculation`, `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_ScoreCalculation` |\n| Zero-time logic | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime_Logic` |\n\n**Testing approach**: Tests use `miniredis` (Redis-compatible in-memory server) with the `valkey-go` client directly -- this works because Valkey is protocol-compatible with Redis.\n\n### 5. Documentation and Planning Files\n\n| File | Path | Purpose |\n|------|------|---------|\n| Proposal | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md` | Business case, scope, alternatives, acceptance criteria |\n| Design | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/design.md` | Full technical design with code snippets (662 lines) |\n| Tasks | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md` | Task breakdown (T1-T5) with checkboxes and acceptance criteria |\n| Delta Spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` | Gherkin-style requirements and scenarios (269 lines) |\n| Session Store Spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-store/spec.md` | Base spec for both Redis and Valkey backends |\n| Session Store Design | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-store/design.md` | Base design for the store package |\n| Root Design | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` | Top-level design doc covering both Redis and Valkey |\n| SDD Prompt | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md` | AI prompt used to generate the design |\n\n### 6. Completed vs Deferred/Incomplete\n\n#### FULLY COMPLETED\n\n1. **Valkey struct and constructor** (`valkeyStore`, `newValkeyStore()`) -- all env var validation working\n2. **All 10 Store interface methods** -- complete implementations matching the design spec\n3. **Singleton integration** -- `STORE_TYPE=valkey` correctly routes to `valkeyStore`\n4. **Unit tests** -- 33 test functions covering validation, CRUD, queries, edge cases, orphan tolerance, interface compliance\n5. **Dependency management** -- `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.0.73` in go.mod\n6. **Codec helpers** -- shared JSON encode/decode for `SandboxInfo`\n7. **Error handling** -- `ErrNotFound` normalization, input validation, batch error propagation\n\n#### DEFERRED / NOT YET IMPLEMENTED (per design.md Section 8 \"Future Changes\")\n\n| Item | Priority | Details |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| **TTL on session keys** | P1 | Session JSON keys have no automatic expiration; cleanup depends entirely on the GC controller calling `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` |\n| **Hash tag support for Valkey Cluster** | P2 | No `{hash-tag}` prefix on keys; MGET would fail in cluster mode across slots. Current workaround: `ListSandboxes` uses individual GET calls instead of MGET |\n| **Metrics** | P2 | No Prometheus/Histogram metrics for operation latency, error rates, or cache hit/miss |\n| **Integration tests with real Valkey** | P2 | Tests use `miniredis` (Redis-compatible); no testcontainers-valkey or live Valkey server tests |\n| **MGET optimization** | P3 | `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` helper (present in Redis, absent in Valkey) was intentionally not implemented for Valkey; `ListSandboxes`/`List*` use individual GET calls per session ID, which is less efficient for large batches |\n\n#### TASK CHECKLIST STATUS (from `changes/AR-014/tasks.md`)\n\nAll tasks in the tasks.md file are marked with `[ ]` (unchecked checkboxes), which appears to be the template format rather than an actual status indicator. Based on code analysis, **all tasks T1 through T5 appear to be fully implemented**:\n\n- **T1** (Constructor): `store_valkey.go` lines 23-59, singleton.go lines 28-33, 4 constructor tests present\n- **T2** (CRUD): All methods implemented (lines 61-149)\n- **T3** (Query): All methods implemented (lines 151-253)\n- **T4** (Tests): 33 test functions in `store_valkey_test.go`\n- **T5** (Gate): Code compiles cleanly, no `log.Printf`, no sensitive data in logs, no TODO markers\n\n### Summary\n\nThe AR-014 Valkey storage implementation is **functionally complete**. All planned Store interface methods are implemented, tested, and integrated into the singleton provider selection. The code is clean with no TODO/FIXME markers. The only deferred items are future enhancements (TTL, hash tags, metrics, integration tests, MGET optimization) that were explicitly listed as lower-priority future work in the design document, not as incomplete parts of the current scope.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_287cd42f4ffeVB604oYQGNV0L1","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore AR-014 Valkey store","time":{"start":1775838084360,"end":1775838219486}}}}
